title: Mexican Beef Tacos Variation 1
method: Fry onion until softened, then add minced beef.
Cook until browned, drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning and a splash of water, cook until thickened.
Fill taco shells with beef, lettuce, tomatoes, and cheese.
Serve immediately with salsa or sour cream.
hydrationTip: Have with sparkling water or a squeeze of lime water to refresh.
